<h4 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h4>
<p>One way to define the absolute value function is <span class="process-math">\(\abs{x}=\sqrt{x^2}\)</span> where his signifies the non-negative square root.  For example, <span class="process-math">\(\abs{3}=\sqrt(3^2)=\sqrt(9)=3\)</span> and <span class="process-math">\(\abs{-3}=\sqrt{(-3)^2}=\sqrt{9}=3\text{.}\)</span></p>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-2.html#p-18" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
</body>
